# Theme Development Guidelines

## Theme System Architecture

The wiki supports 74 themes organized into 10 categories in **[themes/](mdc:themes/)**:

### Theme Categories
1. **Classic Dark** - dark, dracula, halcyon, monokai, night-owl, one-dark-pro, tomorrow-night, zenburn
2. **Classic Light** - atom-one-light, github-light, light, neon-light, solarized-light  
3. **Material Design** - material-darker, material-ocean, material-palenight
4. **Nature & Earth** - ayu-light, bear, everforest-dark, gruvbox-dark/light, kanagawa, rose-pine variants
5. **Arctic & Winter** - nord, nordic, winter-is-coming variants
6. **Ocean & Sky** - ayu variants, base16-ocean, bluloco variants, cobalt2, firefly, iceberg, noctis, oceanic-next, spacegray
7. **Cyberpunk & Neon** - 2077, city-lights, cyberpunk, digital-rain, outrun, snazzy, synthwave-84, tokyo-night, vaporwave
8. **Elegant & Pastel** - andromeda, catppuccin variants, horizon, lucario, moonlight, palenight, shades-of-purple, soft-era, witch-hazel
9. **Professional** - apprentice, corporate-dystopia, flatland, github-dark, material, oxocarbon, protonmail, solarized-dark, thinkultra, vim, vscode-dark-plus
10. **Special Effects** - amber-interface, hackthebox, holographic, hotdog-stand, panda


### Theme Development Rules

#### CSS Structure
- Themes should override CSS custom properties defined in **[style.css](mdc:style.css)**
- Use the established color variable naming convention:
  ```css
  :root {
    --bg-primary: #color;
    --bg-secondary: #color;
    --text-primary: #color;
    --text-secondary: #color;
    --accent-primary: #color;
    --accent-secondary: #color;
    /* etc. */
  }
  ```

#### Theme File Naming
- Use kebab-case: `theme-name.css`
- Special themes: use descriptive prefixes
- Variants: use descriptive suffixes like `-light`, `-dark`, `-soft`

#### Special Effects Guidelines
- Animations should be subtle and not interfere with readability
- Use CSS transforms and transitions, avoid JavaScript-dependent effects
- Consider users who prefer reduced motion (`prefers-reduced-motion`)
- Special effects themes can include:
  - CSS animations and transitions
  - Gradient backgrounds
  - Box shadows and glows
  - Pseudo-element decorations

#### Testing New Themes
- Use **[validate-themes.js](mdc:validate-themes.js)** to validate theme files
- Test theme switching in the application
- Verify readability in both light and dark modes
- Check mobile responsiveness

#### Theme Loading
- Themes are loaded dynamically by the JavaScript in [script.js](mdc:script.js)
- Base path detection handles GitHub/GitLab Pages deployment
- Theme persistence uses localStorage with fallback to `tokyo-night`
